<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
1.7-1.8 mm long (mean = 1.74 mm; n = 5); 2.43-2.83
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the elytral disc flat with short, steep declivity; declivital posterolateral margin carinate; declivity with sparse minor denticles, less abundant than strial punctures, and denticles uniform in size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
